ESTATES OFFICE

Assistant Manager (Facilities and Campus Management) [Role: Assistant Manager (Building Maintenance)] (PR0433/21-22)

The appointee will be responsible for the overall monitoring, coordinating, implementing, supervising and reviewing of repair and maintenance works for on-campus and off-campus premises managed by the University.

Responsibilities:

Liaise with end-users and supervise consultants and contractors;
Prepare tender documents and drawings;
Handle contract administration;
Monitor works programmes, quality/workmanship and budgetary control;
Plan and implement planned maintenance programmes;
Supervise in-house staff and outsourced artisans to maintain high standard of work and output;
Assist in refurbishment and/or improvement projects for on-campus and off-campus premises; and
Perform any other duties as assigned.
Requirements:

A recognised degree in Building Surveying/Building/Construction or a related discipline;
Preferably seven years of relevant work experience;
Knowledge of site practices and current building regulations and statutory requirements in Hong Kong;
Practical experience in AutoCAD application;
Strong communication skills with a very good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese;
Strong problem solving skills and the quality of a good team player and a service-oriented mindset; and
Strong self-motivation with the ability to work independently and under pressure to meet tight schedules.
Shortlisted candidates will be invited to sit for a written test.

Initial appointment will be offered on a fixed-term contract of two years. Re-appointment thereafter will be subject to mutual agreement.

Salary will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.

Application Procedure:

Applicants are invited to submit their applications at the HKBU e-Recruitment System (jobs.hkbu.edu.hk). Those not invited for interview 8 weeks after the closing date may consider their applications unsuccessful. Details of the University’s Personal Information Collection Statement can be found at http://hro.hkbu.edu.hk/pics.

The University reserves the right not to make an appointment for the post advertised, and the appointment will be made according to the terms and conditions then applicable at the time of offer.

Closing date: 28 January 2022

 Responsibilities:

To coordinate with different sub-contractors and supervise the progress of all ABWF works;
To coordinate with the client’s representatives, tenants, Government Departments, Architects, consultant engineers and subcontractors about the detailed site work arrangements, project design change and clarify for the discrepancies;
Responsible for planning and monitoring the work progress;
To attend the site meetings and sub-contractor’s meetings with Architects and consultants;
To coordinate with the Architects, consultant teams and subcontractors for joint site inspections, shop drawing submission, material submission, structural calculation, method statement, Quality Assurance Plan, Environmental and safety plan submissions;
To ensure that quality material is used in the construction of the building.

Requirements:

Higher Diploma or above in Building / Civil / Structural Engineering or equivalent;
1 - 2 years’ relevant experience;
Able to work independently;
With excellent communication, interpersonal and problem-solving skills;
Excellent command of spoken and written English and Chinese.

Competitive remuneration package will be offered to successful candidates. To apply, please send your application with a full resume including current and expected salary, and availability to Corporate Human Services Department, 8/F, KOHO, 73 - 75 Hung To Road, Kwun Tong, Kowloon, Hong Kong or by clicking 'Apply Now' (Please quote the job reference number and job title on the subject).

For more details, please visit our company website  www.hipseng.com

Applicants not invited for interview within 8 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful. Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly in accordance with the company’s personal data policy.

To meet the rapid business expansion, we are looking for an additional new headcount of the QS talents to join our QS team. You will involve the entire tender management from evaluation to arrive the bid decisions and the cost management.   

What we look for?

Execute the cost estimation, cost control and analysis to reach the cost efficiency;
Pricing and estimate the cost of different material needed for the E&M projects;
Responsible for the tender analysis & risk assessment and provide effective solution;
Prepare and ensure tender documents and technical documentations are properly; complied with company policy and standard for tender document submission;
Liaise with clients, or main contractors, or sub-contractors, or government regularly on tender documents, and attend tender meetings;
Deliver the final account settlement;
Coordinate and communicate with internal or external stakeholders.

What you need to succeed?

Higher Diploma/ Degree holder in Quantity Surveying, Engineering or Building Services Engineering;
At least 4 years’ relevant experience in E&M or Building Services industry;
Experience in tendering, budgeting and cost control management is an advantage;
Strong analytical mind, independent and a proactive team player;
Good command of both written and spoken in Chinese and English.

What we offer?

Stable and friendly work environment
Open office design
Annual leave
Medical insurance
Education subsidy
Year-end double pay
Discretionary bonus
Excellent career development
Unlimited beverages and snacks
Internal and external training programme
On-job training

Interested parties, please send your detailed resume with expected salary via “Apply Now” for our consideration

