Responsibilities:

Manage the facilities management service providers to ensure effective and efficient operation of the facilities in newly developed property portfolio in Science Park and Industrial Estates including office buildings, residential institutions, high-tech manufacturing & logistic centre, Data Technology Hub and laboratories;
Review all functions and operations of FM for continuous improvement and working towards FM Best Practices;
Assist to monitor budget implementation;
Monitor the take-over process of new buildings and follow up all outstanding building defects until satisfactory completion;
Administer the tendering process;
Review tender or contract documents submitted by the facility management service providers and advise on the tendering process and tender document formulation;
Comment, inspect and control tenants’ fit-out works and installations.
Comment the design drawings, specifications, manual, etc. and conduct inspections to identify defects during takeover of new projects.
Lead and supervise Technical staff to carry out routine, ad hoc and emergency repair and maintenance works.
Liaise and coordinate on taking over of new properties.
Perform other duties as assigned by Head of Operations and Leasing.

Requirements:

University degree in Surveying, Building Services Engineering or Facilities Management or relevant Engineering disciplines; Master degree in Facilities Management /Engineering is an added advantage;
Corporate membership of HKIS, HKIA, HKIE or equivalent;
Minimum 6 - 8 years’ relevant post qualification working experience in operation and maintenance of large-scale infrastructure; Candidate with less experience will be considered lower position;
Experience in facilities management and contract works with knowledge of Government procedures and requirements on licensing and maintenance certifications;
Experience in handling A&A and fitting out projects and knowledge of relevant statutory requirements;
Working experience with major developer(s);
In-depth knowledge of latest technology of intelligent building and conversant with FM-Maintenance Management System and related software;
Strong interpersonal skills with customer service oriented mindset in dealing with different levels of internal and external parties;
Excellent communication, planning, organizational and management skills; self-motivated, confident, creative and strong desire to achieve better performance;
Proficiency in both written and spoken English and Chinese (including Putonghua);

We offer market competitive compensation, 5-day work week, and generous benefits including medical and life insurance; and voluntary contribution in addition to the legal minimum MPF.  To apply, please send your full resume with current and expected salary to the Human Resources & Office Administration Department, Hong Kong Science and Technology Parks Corporation, 5/F, Building 5E, 5 Science Park East Avenue, Hong Kong Science Park, Hong Kong or, by email via "Apply Now" on or before 27 January 2022.   Please quote the reference number on the email subject/envelope and the application letter. 

Personal data provided will be treated in strict confidence and used for recruitment purpose only.  All personal data collected will be used strictly in accordance with employer’s personal data policies, you can access to HKSTP’s Personal Information Collection Statement at https://www.hkstp.org/hkstp_web/en/hkstp/personal-information-collection-statement-recruitment

Applicants not invited for interview within four weeks after application deadline may consider their applications unsuccessful.  Personal data of unsuccessful applicants will be retained for a maximum of two years. 

